{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀχᾰριστ-ος</b>, ον, <br /> (χᾰρίζομαι) <b>ungracious, unpleasant,</b> οὐκ ἀχάριστα μεθ᾽ ἡμῖν ταῦτ᾽ ἀγορεύεις[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 8.236: irregular _comparative_, δόρπου ἀχαρίστερον (for -ιστότερον) 20.392\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>without grace</b> or <b>charm,</b> οὐκ ἀχάριστα λέγειν[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.1.13; φωνή 4th-3rd c.BC: Epicurus Philosophus “Gnomologium Vaticanum - Kleine Schriften” 75\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; -ότερον ἐπιμέλημα a <b>more thankless</b> business, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 7.37; ἀ. ἐξέτασις 1st c.BC: Dionysius Halicarnassensis “Epistula ad Pompeium” 1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> of persons, <b>ungracious, unfavourable,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 6th c.BC: Theognis Elegiacus 841 (-τως Bgk.), 1st c.BC: Philodemus Gadarensis Epigrammaticus “Ir.” p.60 W. \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> <b>ungrateful, thankless,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.90, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 1.2.7, 4th c.BC: Crates Thebanus Poeta Philosophus 19, etc.; δῆμος 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.91; προδότας 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 880 (Lyric poetry), compare “Med.” 659 (Lyric poetry); ἀ. πρὸς τοὺς γονέας 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Memorabilia” 2.2.14; τινί 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hecuba” 138 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σπείρων εἰς ἀχάριστα sowingin <b>thankless soil,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" Inscriptiones Graecae 14.2012 (Sulp. 1st c.BC(?): Maximus Astrologus)\">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]. <i>adverb</i> -τως, ἀποπέμψασθαι εὐεργέτας[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 7.7.23, compare 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 30.6. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.3</b></Level3> <i>passive</i>, <b>unrequited,</b> ἀ. εἶναι τὰ ἀνηλωμένα[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Lysias Orator 21.12. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<i>adverb</i> οὐκ ἂν ἀχαρίστως μοι ἔχοι πρός τινος <b>thanks</b> would not be <b>refused</b> me by.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Anabasis” 2.3.18. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.4</b></Level3> <i>adverb</i> -τως <b>with a bad grace, with an ill will,</b> ἀ. ἕπεσθαι follow <b>sulkily,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyr.” 7.4.14; τὰς χάριτας ἀ. χαρίζεσθαι 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 1.31. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.5</b></Level3> ἀχάριστον, τό, <b>antidote,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" PGrenf. 1.52.1,12 (3rd c.AD), Marcell. Empir.20: also ἀχάριστος, ἡ, 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor Trall. “Febr.” 7. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level4><b>__II.5.b</b></Level4> name of an <b>eyesalve,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.AD: Celsus Medicus 6.6.7, 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus 12.749.\">Refs 1st c.AD+</a>]","strongNumber":"G0884","accentedUnicode":"ἀχάριστος","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G5483","matchingForm":"χαρίζω","stepTransliteration":"charizō","gloss":"to give grace","_zh_tw_Gloss":"赦免","_es_Gloss":"dar gracia","_zh_Gloss":"赦免"}],"shortDef":"ungrateful","mediumDef":"<b>unthankful, ungrateful,</b> <ref='Luk.6.35'>Lk. 6:35</ref>; <ref='2Ti.3.2'>2Tim. 3:2</ref>*","stepGloss":"ungrateful","stepTransliteration":"acharistos","count":2,"_es_Definition":"ingrato, desagradecido","_zh_tw_Definition":"不知感激的, 忘恩負義的 (路 6:35; 提後 3:2)","_zh_Definition":"不知感激的, 忘恩负义的 (路 6:35; 提后 3:2)","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"vô ơn ; không biết ơn","_zh_tw_Gloss":"忘恩","_es_Gloss":"ingrato","_zh_Gloss":"忘恩"}]}